#----- Armor

#----- Mwk Armor

base item with armor Mwk Armor =

  synonyms          "Masterwork Armor", "Armor, Masterwork";
  check penalty     +1;
  value             150 gp;
  probability       Uncommon;
  appearances       Common "Good workmanship.",
                    Common "Finely crafted.",
                    Common "Well made.",
                    Rare "Extraordinarily well made.";
  player name       "";
  references        WTC 17524: 126;
  description
  "Just as with weapons, you can purchase or craft masterwork versions of armor
  or shields. Such a well-made item functions like the normal version, except
  that its armor check penalty is lessened by 1.

  A masterwork suit of armor or shield costs an extra 150 gp over and above the
  normal cost for that type of armor or shield.

  The masterwork quality of a suite of armor never provides a bonus on attack
  or damage rolls, even if the armor or shield is used as a weapon (such as
  \Item{spiked armor} or a \Item{spiked shield}).

  All magic armors and shields are automatically considered to be of masterwork
  quality.

  You can't add the masterwork quality to armor or a shield after it is
  created; it must be created as a masterwork item.";
  short description "A masterwork version.";
  synonyms          "Masterwork";
  categories        masterwork.

