#----- Ring of Counterspells

base item Ring of Counterspells =

  base              Ring;
  value             4000 gp;
  probability       Rare;
  references        WTC 17752: 230;
  description
  "This ring might seem to be a ring of spell storing upon first
  examination. However, while it allows a single spell of 1st through 6th level
  to be cast into it, that spell cannot be cast out of the ring again. Instead,
  should that spell ever be cast upon the wearer, the spell is immediately
  countered, as a counterspell action, requiring no action (or even knowledge)
  on the wearer's part. Once so used, the spell cast within the ring is
  gone. A new spell (or the same one as before) may be placed in it again.";
  short description "The spell stored in this ring is automatically countered when cast upon the wearer, with no action required.";
  synonyms          "Counterspells, Ring of";
  categories        spell,
                    counter,
                    magic,
                    ring.

