  spheres. The spheres are detachable by the wearer (and only by the wearer),
  who can easily hurl one of them up to 70 feet. When a sphere arrives at the
  end of its trajectory, it detonates as a \Spell{fireball} spell (Reflex DC 14
  half).  Spheres come in different strengths, ranging from those that deal 2d6
  points of fire damage to those that deal 10d6.

  If the necklace is being worn or carried by a character who fails her saving
  throw against a magical fire attack, the item must make a saving throw as
  well (with a save bonus of +7). If the necklace fails to save, all its
  remaining spheres detonate simultaneously, often with regrettable
  consequences for the wearer.".

